raw._content: 980211-F-2352G-014 .	The 615th Air Mobility Group uses forklifts to unload equipment from a U.S. Air Force a C-5 Galaxy at an operating base in Southwest Asia on Feb. 11, 1998.  U.S. Air Force personnel from the 715th and 815th Air Mobility Squadron will operate as a Tanker Airlift Control Element, commonly called a TALCE, to control all U.S. airlift traffic in and out of their deployed location in support of Operation Southern Watch which is the U.S. and coalition enforcement of the no-fly-zone over Southern Iraq.  The 615th, 715th and 815th are deployed from Travis Air Force Base, Calif.  DoD photo by Staff Sgt. Efrain Gonzalez, U.S. Air Force..
